jp.ac.keio.bio.fun.xitosbml.util

Class ModelValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • jp.ac.keio.bio.fun.xitosbml.util.ModelValidator

  • public class ModelValidator
extends Object
    The class ModelValidator, which is an utility class to validate SBML document. The saved SBML file will contain an annotation generated by this class. The annotation contains following information:
    • Model ID
    • Hostname
    • Date
    • XitoSBML version and credit
    Date Created: Feb 21, 2017
    Author:
    Kaito Ii <ii@fun.bio.keio.ac.jp>, Akira Funahashi <funa@bio.keio.ac.jp>

    • Method Detail

      • validate

        public void validate()
        Validate the SBML document. This method will will check whether the SBML document has correct level, version and extension. Checking missing boundary conditions for Species is also done by this method. Moreover, if XitoSBML is connected to an internet, then this method will send the model to the online SBML validator, which will run a semantic validation, and show the validation result.

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Example main() method which will read an SBML file and execute a validation. This example requires a specific SBML model "test.xml" located under the specific directory.
        Parameters:
        args - an array of command-line arguments for the application
